# validate-wave-status wiring rule

Use `signalos validate-wave-status [--wave W<n>]` before treating a Wave as
ready for merge, release, or closeout.

- `signalos status` is advisory and may exit 0 while work remains.
- `signalos validate-wave-status` is blocking and exits 1 when Journey blockers
  remain.
- Gate artifacts must be present, signed, hash-valid, audit-linked, and signed
  by an allowed role for that artifact.
- If `--wave` is provided, every gate audit link must carry the same normalized
  wave id.
- Do not pass `--api-url` unless the app runtime has a technology-independent
  status API; current app validation is local-file based.
